	<h4> Introduction </h4>
	<p>
		This API was designed by Tristan Waddington and represents a personal development of a web interface to search the Oregon Liquor Control Commissions' (OLCC) monthly pricing updates. The OLCC does not provide their own web API for this information, but provides data tables. This API (and corresponding <a href="http://www.oregonliquorprices.com"> web interface </a>) is meant to provide a means of accessing that data easily.
	</p>

 	<h4> What it Does </h4>
	<p>
		Every month the OLCC publishes a listing of current prices of their liquor, and store inventory for all the stores in Oregon. This information comes out in tables, and can be accessed by anyone at their <a href="http://www.oregon.gov/OLCC/pages/index.aspx"> official homepage </a>. The web service parses the table when it is published, and updates its information based on the official publication. The information can be then accessed by the web interface provided, or can be retrieved in JSON format via this API. The data is separated into 3 different organziational structures: Price, Product, and Store.
	</p>
	
	<h4> Price </h4>
	<p>
	Price is the first URI category that we can segragate our liquor into. The API supports returning a price list filtered by product, or an unfiltered list. To access the list, an HTTP GET request is made to:<br>
	<div class="codeWrap"><code>http://www.oregonliquorprices.com/api/v1/price/</code></div><br>
	The get request can include two types of queries:<br>
	<ul>
		<li>limit - the number of items returned in the list </li>
		<li>offset - the starting index you wish to return your index at </li>
	</ul>

	Here is an example tool that will illustrate the information you receive back:
	</p>

